SECTION-BY-SECTION ANALYSIS OF THE LEGISLATION
Section 1. Short title
Section 1 provides the short title is the ‘‘Expanding Access to
Capital for Rural Job Creators Act.’’
Section 2. Access to capital for rural-area small businesses
Section 2 amends the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 to add
rural area businesses to those businesses that the SEC’s Advocate
for Small Business Capital Formation is required to identify prob-
lems faced by when they are securing access to capital.
